hmMgmtSESPendingReturn.name: hmMgmtSESPendingReturn
hmMgmtSESPendingReturn.description: Indicates that the Operation is still pending.

hmMgmtSESTestReturn.name: hmMgmtSESTestReturn
hmMgmtSESTestReturn.description: Indicates an error on a write to the attribute hmMgmtSETestVar. Two parameters are expected. The fist parameter is the length of the value, the second parameter is the value itself. The parameter length is {0}. The parameter is {1}.

hmMgmtSESpinLock.name: hmMgmtSESpinLock
hmMgmtSESpinLock.description: An advisory lock which is used as an generator to get a unique Identifier for a SET-PDU. This allows the Agent to write additional Information of the Status of the SET-PDU.

hmMgmtSEReturnTable.name: hmMgmtSEReturnTable
hmMgmtSEReturnTable.description: The table of additional Information (enterprise specific Errors or pending) of a SET-PDU.

hmMgmtSeReturnKey.name: hmMgmtSeReturnKey
hmMgmtSeReturnKey.description: Contains the Value of hmMgmtSESpinLock of the corresponding SET-PDU which are responsible for this table entry.

hmMgmtSeReturnCode.name: hmMgmtSeReturnCode
hmMgmtSeReturnCode.description: Contains an additional Information to the SET-PDU. Can contain the ObjectIdentity under hmMgmtSESReturns or any other ObjectIdentity in enterprise specific MIBs.

hmMgmtSEParameterTable.name: hmMgmtSEParameterTable
hmMgmtSEParameterTable.description: The table of additional Parameter the HmMgmtSEReturnTable for the specific message.

hmMgmtSEParameterID.name: hmMgmtSEParameterID
hmMgmtSEParameterID.description: A unique identifier (with hmMgmtSeReturnKey) for this entry.

hmMgmtSEParameterValue.name: hmMgmtSEParameterValue
hmMgmtSEParameterValue.description: The Information for the Wildcard for the corresponding message. Link between these two tables is hmMgmtSeReturnKey. The hmMgmtSEParameterID denotes the wildcard position.

hmMgmtSETestVar.name: hmMgmtSETestVar
hmMgmtSETestVar.description: Test variable to check the functionality of extended error handling. Setting a value to this attribute MUST return hmMgmtSESTestReturn with specific parameter.
